comment: 5: Will you remain below your corruption limit if you put on the new gear?
The more corruption you have, the worse downsides you experience
Well, I guess it gives some prestige to those dedicated enough to understand the mechanics of the system.
1 - 19: When you take damage, you have a chance to be slowed for 5 seconds.  The slow's magnitude increases with corruption

20 - 39 corruption: Your spells and abilities have a chance to summon an Eye of Corruption for 8 seconds.  It will inflict increasing damage every 2 seconds you are within range.  Range and damage increases with corruption.
40 - 59:  Taking damage has a chance to summon a Thing from Beyond to pursue you for 8 seconds.  Speed increases with corruption.

60 - 79: If you are struck by a Thing from Beyond, you are immediately afflicted by Grasping Tendrils (tier 1) and Eye of Corruption (tier 2).  And this thing will nuke your health even without this tier...
80+: You gain the Inevitable Doom debuff, increasing damage taken and reducing healing received.
At 80, it starts at 5%, and goes up 1% for every additional point of corruption.
See the problem with this system?
Yeah, some of it is no-want
What a mixed bag of effects.
lol, also Trace's estate is pretty seriously corrupted then it has both a seeing eye of corruption and some wayward tendrils.
It's more or less (stay at tier 1 or lower, or we boot your ass from the raid)
It's not uncommon for raid bosses to have mechanics that require your ass to move out of an attack, stay within a very limited range, or not move very much
Yeah, you can do more damage if you have more corruption buffs, but if you die, know how much damage you do? ZERO.
Additionally, these effects will put more strain on the healers to keep corrupted players alive, which could also result in failed attempts
It's like... noobs aren't gonna understand how bad they're screwing themselves over, and hardcore people are going to burn out trying to maximize the new system
I don't see this going past 8.3.
way to throw a wrench in things
Also, I don't like the visual effects of corruption
SO I refuse to go above 0 :P
Also, you can't NOT use corrupted items
This patch introduced a new legendary cloak (huge reference to MoP) that gives corruption resistance
And there are new azerite traits that give it as well.  As it stands, I'm at 30 corruption resistance, so I lose out by NOT using at least 1 corrupted item.
So it's just an extra headache all-around
